<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 2:54PM EDT  by NWS Newport/Morehead City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Jones, south central
Lenoir, southwestern Craven, northern Onslow and eastern Duplin
Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 254 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Potters Hill, or 15 miles northwest of Half Moon, moving east at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
New Bern, River Bend, Phillips Crossroads, Richlands, Maysville,
Comfort, Belgrade, Rhems, Petersburg, Pleasant Hill, Deppe, Loco VFD,
Pollocksville, Hargetts Crossroads and Trenton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
